CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 20, 1961, pg. 2, reads: "Third Ward "Blues" - William Pope (left), Third Ward independent candidate for constable, and A. J. Scott, aldermanic candidate, who also lost, appeared at the Ninth District, Third Ward polls, at Letsche School, when deputy sheriffs were sent up to settle a dispute between workers around the poll."
TitMainTitle: William Pope, A. J. Scott, and unknown woman, standing in front of Letsche School with campaign posters including one listing Democratic Primary candidates, during 1961 primary elections
